      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "Are we seeing large NOTFOUND messages in the wild?\n\nRather than banning, perhaps we should just process them more efficiently? Something like:\n\n```diff\n--- a/src/net_processing.cpp\n+++ b/src/net_processing.cpp\n@@ -5149,17 +5149,19 @@ void PeerManagerImpl::ProcessMessage(Peer& peer, CNode& pfrom, const std::string\n\n     if (msg_type == NetMsgType::NOTFOUND) {\n         std::vector<CInv> vInv;\n-        vRecv >> vInv;\n-        std::vector<GenTxid> tx_invs;\n-        if (vInv.size() <= node::MAX_PEER_TX_ANNOUNCEMENTS + MAX_BLOCKS_IN_TRANSIT_PER_PEER) {\n-            for (CInv &inv : vInv) {\n+        unsigned int n_inv = ReadCompactSize(vRecv);\n+        if (n_inv <= node::MAX_PEER_TX_ANNOUNCEMENTS + MAX_BLOCKS_IN_TRANSIT_PER_PEER) {\n+            std::vector<GenTxid> tx_invs;\n+            while (n_inv-- > 0) {\n+                CInv inv;\n+                vRecv >> inv;\n                 if (inv.IsGenTxMsg()) {\n                     tx_invs.emplace_back(ToGenTxid(inv));\n                 }\n             }\n+            LOCK(m_tx_download_mutex);\n+            m_txdownloadman.ReceivedNotFound(pfrom.GetId(), tx_invs);\n         }\n-        LOCK(m_tx_download_mutex);\n-        m_txdownloadman.ReceivedNotFound(pfrom.GetId(), tx_invs);\n         return;\n     }\n```",
